The paper deals with dynamic programming on trees, which is a topic that falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on parallelizing dynamic programming algorithms, the most likely categories are cs.DC and cs.DS, followed by cs.DM and cs.CC, and finally cs.LG.
